    <title>Combinatorial description of the roots of the Bernstein-Sato polynomials
  for monomial ideals</title>
    <summary>  We give a combinatorial description of the roots of the Bernstein-Sato
polynomial of a monomial ideal using the Newton polyhedron and some semigroups
associated to the ideal.
</summary>
